T-Test

The p-value being small enough to be 0, hence as used a two-sided test we can reject the null hypothesis that the means of BMI being equal between male and female athletes. The plots indicate that male Olympian athletes’ BMI to be than female Olympian Athletes. Female and male athletes BMI: 21.4, 23.4
